
  <sn><md>## Rock {.text-end}
---

:::.row

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
A rock is a `naturally occurring solid mass` made of minerals or mineraloids, classified by its composition, minerals, and formation process. Rocks make up the Earth's crust and most of its interior, excluding the liquid core. The **study of rocks**, known as `petrology` and mineralogy, may include Earth and other celestial bodies.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-6
![mount-sinar](https://i.pinimg.com/originals/2c/66/74/2c66746999b87e2d7caa994938a71fee.jpg)
:::

:::


Rocks are divided into three main types:

* **Igneous rocks** – formed by `cooling of magma or lava`.
* **Sedimentary rocks** – formed by `compaction and cementation of sediments` from weathered rocks.
* **Metamorphic rocks** – formed when `existing rocks change under high heat and pressure` without melting.

Humans have used rocks `since the Stone Age` for tools, construction, and mining. Modern technology has also created artificial rock-like materials such as concrete.
